AmaZing Vietnamese food in Waikiki! Found this place by chance because it was around the corner from where I was staying. Their banh mi is delicious, too, chock full of pickled veggies, tender meat and plenty of cilantro (as it should be!)  I’d ignore a lot of these one-star reviews, people moaning because they didn’t open right on time or the lady at the counter was curt with them (to that person I say, do not go to Vietnam if that style of speaking intimidates you… this isn’t the Cheesecake Factory) but no one can argue with the quality of ingredients and overall taste, which is superb, nor the reasonable prices, which are hard to find on this part of Oahu. Highly recommended.
